<dl id="n12006h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12006h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12006h"> 6(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> when he sinks &mdash; E of W</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Lui aussi, comme certains de ses semblables, s&apos;enfonce en terre. On ne s&apos;en aper&ccedil;oit pas; depuis un si&egrave;cle, il n&apos;a pas diminu&eacute; d&apos;un millim&egrave;tre, et c&apos;est fort heureux pour le genre humain, car les habitants des alentours affirment que <mark>&ldquo; l&apos;heure du jugement dernier sonnera, quand le menhir du Champ-Dolent dispara&icirc;tra&rdquo;</mark>. <br><font color="green">[Like other rocks, it sinks into the ground. This cannot be perceived; after one century it has not gone down one millimetre&mdash;a good thing for all of humanity because the inhabitants of the area claim that &ldquo;judgement day will arrive when the menhir of Champ-Dolent disappears&rdquo;.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 20</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: E of W = End of World. </mm> </dd></dl>
